---

olive oil
1 packet cherry tomatoes
1 packet green beans
1 packet Beef Rump
½ tbs brown sugar
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
½ packet Dijon mustard
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet diced bacon

• Halve cherry tomatoes. Trim and halve green beans.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook green beans, until tender, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

• Meanwhile, place beef rump between two sheets of baking paper. Pound beef with a meat mallet or rolling pin until slightly flattened. Season beef generously with salt and pepper.
• Return frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef, turning, for 5-6 minutes (depending on thickness), or until cooked to your liking.
• Remove pan from heat, add the brown sugar, balsamic vinegar and a splash of water and turn to coat. Transfer to a plate to rest.
• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 4-6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.

TIP: Pounding the beef ensures that it's extra tender once cooked.

• To the bowl with the green beans, add dijon mustard (see ingredients), cherry tomatoes, mixed salad leaves, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Sprinkle with diced bacon and toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Thinly slice beef.
• Divide bacon cherry tomato salad between bowls. Top with balsamic glazed beef rump. Enjoy!